00:01:46.852 --> 00:01:50.573
- So, some of you know my
interests in anthropogeny,

00:01:50.573 --> 00:01:53.960
originated from studies in
sialic acid, biology changes,

00:01:53.960 --> 00:01:55.627
and human evolution.

00:01:56.564 --> 00:01:58.105
And my background as a physician

00:01:58.105 --> 00:02:02.383
led me to explore human specific diseases.

00:02:02.383 --> 00:02:04.023
So, what, then, am I doing here,

00:02:04.023 --> 00:02:07.690
talking about death
awareness and mortality?

00:02:09.045 --> 00:02:11.545
In 2005, I lectured at
the University of Arizona,

00:02:11.545 --> 00:02:13.158
and ventured beyond my expertise,

00:02:13.158 --> 00:02:16.968
of pining about the
evolution of human cognition.

00:02:16.968 --> 00:02:17.969
At the lunch that followed,

00:02:17.969 --> 00:02:21.360
a local professor sat next to me and said,

00:02:21.360 --> 00:02:25.127
"You are all asking the wrong question!"

00:02:25.127 --> 00:02:26.947
Danny Brower's point was, perhaps,

00:02:26.947 --> 00:02:30.459
we should not be asking
how human minds evolved.

00:02:30.459 --> 00:02:31.629
There have been highly-intelligent,

00:02:31.629 --> 00:02:33.576
warm-blooded social creatures around

00:02:33.576 --> 00:02:35.997
for tens of thousands of years.

00:02:35.997 --> 00:02:39.419
Elephants, carver birds,
apes and dolphins.

00:02:39.419 --> 00:02:40.713
So, why are we not having to compete

00:02:40.713 --> 00:02:42.919
with these other species?

00:02:42.919 --> 00:02:44.503
Danny suggested that it's not just

00:02:44.503 --> 00:02:48.471
that something unusual happened
during human evolution,

00:02:48.471 --> 00:02:50.181
but also, that all these other species

00:02:50.181 --> 00:02:53.034
were blocked in progression,

00:02:53.034 --> 00:02:56.401
by a cognitive barrier that
only we had broken through.

00:02:56.401 --> 00:02:58.466
So, I was really intrigued
by this contrarian view,

00:02:58.466 --> 00:03:01.660
and we talked a long time
after everyone was gone.

00:03:01.660 --> 00:03:04.699
And I strongly recommended
that he publish.

00:03:04.699 --> 00:03:06.629
Seeing nothing in print,
after more than a year,

00:03:06.629 --> 00:03:10.158
I followed up with
emails, got no responses,

00:03:10.158 --> 00:03:12.509
looked up his phone
number on the Internet,

00:03:12.509 --> 00:03:14.676
only to find his obituary.

00:03:17.020 --> 00:03:18.338
Danny had died, very suddenly,

00:03:18.338 --> 00:03:21.106
of an unusual disease,
called aortic dissection.

00:03:21.106 --> 00:03:23.036
I contact his friend, Sean Carroll,

00:03:23.036 --> 00:03:24.758
who said Danny had indeed been working

00:03:24.758 --> 00:03:27.486
on some novel idea, but never published.

00:03:27.486 --> 00:03:29.990
After more than two decades
of exploring anthropogeny,

00:03:29.990 --> 00:03:33.241
I could see some real important
potential in Danny's idea,

00:03:33.241 --> 00:03:36.491
and I just could not let it die with him.

00:03:36.491 --> 00:03:38.891
Fortunately, the editor of
Nature, Philip Campbell,

00:03:38.891 --> 00:03:40.142
allowed me to write a letter

00:03:40.142 --> 00:03:42.383
about Danny's idea, with
some embellishments.

00:03:42.383 --> 00:03:43.474
I thought I had done my duty,

00:03:43.474 --> 00:03:46.391
and could leave it to
experts, to follow up.

00:03:46.391 --> 00:03:47.224
But a week later,

00:03:47.224 --> 00:03:50.406
I got an email from Danny
Brower's widow, Sharon,

00:03:50.406 --> 00:03:51.700
thanking me for writing the letter,

00:03:51.700 --> 00:03:53.831
told me that Danny has started a book,

00:03:53.831 --> 00:03:55.957
and asked if I would like to read it.

00:03:55.957 --> 00:03:57.965
Looking at his draft, I
realized that his thinking

00:03:57.965 --> 00:04:00.496
had progressed very much
in the way mine had,

00:04:00.496 --> 00:04:03.779
and we had come to very similar
conclusions, independently.

00:04:03.779 --> 00:04:06.998
But, there were great challenges
in completing this book.

00:04:06.998 --> 00:04:10.469
First, one author was dead.
(crowd laughing)

00:04:10.469 --> 00:04:12.556
And the other wanted to
preserve the original intent

00:04:12.556 --> 00:04:14.048
and prose.

00:04:14.048 --> 00:04:17.080
Second, I really had no time
to do full justice to it,

00:04:17.080 --> 00:04:18.805
because of my lack of expertise,

00:04:18.805 --> 00:04:21.365
and also, lack of time.

00:04:21.365 --> 00:04:23.734
And last, but not least,
who would care about a book

00:04:23.734 --> 00:04:26.172
by a dead insect geneticist,

00:04:26.172 --> 00:04:27.762
and a living physician-scientist,

00:04:27.762 --> 00:04:30.169
who claim to have
explained the human mind?

00:04:30.169 --> 00:04:32.250
(crowd laughing)

00:04:32.250 --> 00:04:33.843
So, I sat on this for a while,

00:04:33.843 --> 00:04:36.272
but, fortunately, a friend
of mine, Abraham Verghese,

00:04:36.272 --> 00:04:39.654
an author, put me in touch
with his agent, Mary Evans,

00:04:39.654 --> 00:04:41.723
who saw the potential in the book,

00:04:41.723 --> 00:04:44.440
and contacted Cary
Goldstein of Twelve Books,

00:04:44.440 --> 00:04:46.509
to help me with it.

00:04:46.509 --> 00:04:48.538
And so, I went on.

00:04:48.538 --> 00:04:52.619
Strike four, was I wouldn't
talk about a Superstorm Sandy.

00:04:52.619 --> 00:04:54.851
Strike five, was poor
follow-through on my part,

00:04:54.851 --> 00:04:58.012
because of lack of
expertise, and lack of time.

00:04:58.012 --> 00:04:59.524
(crowd laughing)

00:04:59.524 --> 00:05:01.283
And last, but not least, was a book title

00:05:01.283 --> 00:05:05.366
that the publisher insisted
on, which was Denial.

00:05:07.155 --> 00:05:08.306
So, for a while, I thought that this

00:05:08.306 --> 00:05:11.331
was a hackneyed, old phrase,
that had so many meanings,

00:05:11.331 --> 00:05:14.254
that it didn't really
say what I wanted to say.

00:05:14.254 --> 00:05:16.167
And in fact, if you looked on Amazon,

00:05:16.167 --> 00:05:18.605
you would find not only
the famous, important book,

00:05:18.605 --> 00:05:21.966
related to this topic, Denial of Death,

00:05:21.966 --> 00:05:23.937
but numerous books with
the word denial in them.

00:05:23.937 --> 00:05:26.317
(crowd laughing)

00:05:26.317 --> 00:05:27.150
The more I thought about it,

00:05:27.150 --> 00:05:31.028
I'd realize that, actually,
the publisher and agent

00:05:31.028 --> 00:05:32.647
were right.

00:05:32.647 --> 00:05:35.265
All these books are talking,
really, about various versions

00:05:35.265 --> 00:05:37.207
of the same phenomenon,

00:05:37.207 --> 00:05:40.539
the human penchant for denying reality.

00:05:40.539 --> 00:05:42.257
And, in fact, as you read more,

00:05:42.257 --> 00:05:46.498
I found other books by
many famous authors,

00:05:46.498 --> 00:05:47.897
all of which, are on different topics,

00:05:47.897 --> 00:05:50.736
but all contain pieces of the same story,

00:05:50.736 --> 00:05:53.955
a human ability to ignore reality.

00:05:53.955 --> 00:05:56.195
Let me give you some practical examples.

00:05:56.195 --> 00:05:58.460
As a physician, I am
acutely aware of the fact

00:05:58.460 --> 00:06:01.754
that lack of exercise,
unhealthy diet, tobacco use,

00:06:01.754 --> 00:06:05.425
ignoring obesity, high
blood pressure, sleep apnea,

00:06:05.425 --> 00:06:09.846
poor hygiene, and excessive
red meat are bad for you.

00:06:09.846 --> 00:06:13.227
But, I'm not gonna ask for
a show of hands, because...

00:06:13.227 --> 00:06:15.375
(crowd laughing)

00:06:15.375 --> 00:06:19.363
Physicians, like myself,
are equally guilty.

00:06:19.363 --> 00:06:21.894
Then, we have massive denial
of scientific reality.

00:06:21.894 --> 00:06:25.893
Biological evolution, climate
change, magical cures,

00:06:25.893 --> 00:06:28.816
vaccines don't work, worse,
still, they cause autism,

00:06:28.816 --> 00:06:33.106
despite of being
debunked, UFOs, of course,

00:06:33.106 --> 00:06:35.335
weird cancer risks, not real ones,

00:06:35.335 --> 00:06:37.887
and here, in San Diego,
fluoride in the waters,

00:06:37.887 --> 00:06:39.196
a Communist plot.

00:06:39.196 --> 00:06:42.708
(crowd laughing)

00:06:42.708 --> 00:06:44.731
And then, there are many
examples of societal denial

00:06:44.731 --> 00:06:46.057
of practical reality.

00:06:46.057 --> 00:06:50.748
National debt, each of
you owes 150,000 dollars.

00:06:50.748 --> 00:06:54.776
Health care costs, end of
life costs, covert racism,

00:06:54.776 --> 00:06:57.769
population growth, and
insistence on rebuilding,

00:06:57.769 --> 00:07:00.459
in exactly the places where
the worth earthquakes, floods,

00:07:00.459 --> 00:07:02.792
and hurricanes have occured.

00:07:04.955 --> 00:07:07.498
And then, of course, the
examples of political distortion

00:07:07.498 --> 00:07:10.505
of reality.
(crowd laughing)

00:07:10.505 --> 00:07:11.413
I'm not gonna read this slide.

00:07:11.413 --> 00:07:12.893
You know what I'm talking about.

00:07:12.893 --> 00:07:14.701
(crowd laughing)

00:07:14.701 --> 00:07:17.029
But, to be fair, there
are plenty of examples

00:07:17.029 --> 00:07:18.690
of distortion of reality,

00:07:18.690 --> 00:07:21.740
at the other end of
the political spectrum.

00:07:21.740 --> 00:07:24.300
I think Calvin puts it well to Hobbes.

00:07:24.300 --> 00:07:25.908
"It's not denial.

00:07:25.908 --> 00:07:28.726
"I'm just very selective
about the reality I accept."

00:07:28.726 --> 00:07:32.026
(crowd laughing)

00:07:32.026 --> 00:07:35.257
So, after writing the book,
I had much difficulty,

00:07:35.257 --> 00:07:36.807
finding a single word, or phrase,

00:07:36.807 --> 00:07:38.507
that encompasses phenomenons,

00:07:38.507 --> 00:07:41.366
and when to use the phrase
identified in the dictionary,

00:07:41.366 --> 00:07:43.047
reality denial,

00:07:43.047 --> 00:07:44.440
which I'm defining as some kind of

00:07:44.440 --> 00:07:46.405
subconscious defense mechanism,

00:07:46.405 --> 00:07:49.085
characterized by refusal to acknowledge,

00:07:49.085 --> 00:07:52.245
or rationalization of
unwanted, or unpleasant facts,

00:07:52.245 --> 00:07:54.637
realities, thoughts, or feelings.

00:07:54.637 --> 00:07:57.388
Now, so, I think we have
to add reality denial

00:07:57.388 --> 00:07:59.847
to the long list of
unusual and exaggerated

00:07:59.847 --> 00:08:01.556
cognitive features of humans,

00:08:01.556 --> 00:08:03.869
some of which, are listed here.

00:08:03.869 --> 00:08:05.219
But, for most of these other features,

00:08:05.219 --> 00:08:08.136
we can think of good reasons
why they might have evolved,

00:08:08.136 --> 00:08:10.513
in terms of benefiting humans.

00:08:10.513 --> 00:08:12.696
But, at the reality
denial, there's a mystery.

00:08:12.696 --> 00:08:15.578
Excessive reality denial are
the kind that humans practice,

00:08:15.578 --> 00:08:18.167
should be an evolutionary maladaptation.

00:08:18.167 --> 00:08:19.990
Excessive reality denial should result

00:08:19.990 --> 00:08:21.995
in excessive risk taking
in the individuals

00:08:21.995 --> 00:08:23.821
who have the genetic ability to do that,

00:08:23.821 --> 00:08:27.722
should disappear.
(crowd laughing)

00:08:27.722 --> 00:08:30.392
So, how, and why, did
excessive reality denial

00:08:30.392 --> 00:08:32.891
risk taking evolve in humans?

00:08:32.891 --> 00:08:37.367
And what benefits outweigh
those negative consequences?

00:08:37.367 --> 00:08:40.217
So now, this brings me another
extension of Danny's idea,

00:08:40.217 --> 00:08:43.648
that the independent
evolution of self-awareness,

00:08:43.648 --> 00:08:45.401
in the very same intelligent creatures

00:08:45.401 --> 00:08:47.241
that we've discussed before,

00:08:47.241 --> 00:08:49.209
although, lots of arguments
about the techniques

00:08:49.209 --> 00:08:51.159
used in the real conclusions,

00:08:51.159 --> 00:08:54.050
it's reasonably clear that chimpanzees,

00:08:54.050 --> 00:08:57.510
and perhaps, elephants,
dolphins and magpies,

00:08:57.510 --> 00:08:59.452
can recognize themselves in the mirror,

00:08:59.452 --> 00:09:01.243
and have some kind of sense of self.

00:09:01.243 --> 00:09:03.970
It's hard to define exactly what it is.

00:09:03.970 --> 00:09:06.020
But, they certainly do have this.

00:09:06.020 --> 00:09:10.191
So, are animals and birds with
awareness of their own self,

00:09:10.191 --> 00:09:12.060
also aware of the self-awareness

00:09:12.060 --> 00:09:14.222
of others of their own kind?

00:09:14.222 --> 00:09:16.193
I asked myself that question,
and did some reading,

00:09:16.193 --> 00:09:18.663
and realized I was
thinking about something

00:09:18.663 --> 00:09:21.763
that's been well-studied,
called theory of mind,

00:09:21.763 --> 00:09:24.384
the ability to attribute
mental beliefs, desires,

00:09:24.384 --> 00:09:27.420
intentions, and perspectives, to oneself,

00:09:27.420 --> 00:09:29.800
and to others, and to
understand that others, also,

00:09:29.800 --> 00:09:32.331
have beliefs, desires,
intentions, and perspectives,

00:09:32.331 --> 00:09:35.500
that are similar, or
different, from one's own.

00:09:35.500 --> 00:09:36.664
There are many other related terms,

00:09:36.664 --> 00:09:39.392
intentionality, et cetera,
that I won't go through.

00:09:39.392 --> 00:09:41.534
But, they are overlapping terms.

00:09:41.534 --> 00:09:44.503
After reading further, I
realized there's a continuum

00:09:44.503 --> 00:09:46.767
in the cognitive development
of theory of mind,

00:09:46.767 --> 00:09:48.520
and intentionality.

00:09:48.520 --> 00:09:51.429
A two year old human
passes the mirror test.

00:09:51.429 --> 00:09:52.401
A three-to-four year old human

00:09:52.401 --> 00:09:56.182
has a more rudimentary
theory of mind, that emerges.

00:09:56.182 --> 00:09:58.668
A five year old human has
a full theory of mind,

00:09:58.668 --> 00:10:02.835
and can tell excellent lies.
(crowd laughing)

00:10:05.477 --> 00:10:07.645
But, adult humans have
something that I might call

00:10:07.645 --> 00:10:11.485
extended theory of mind, or
multi-order intentionality.

00:10:11.485 --> 00:10:13.714
Their ability to do what
we are doing right now.

00:10:13.714 --> 00:10:16.466
You're reading my mind,
I'm reading your mind,

00:10:16.466 --> 00:10:18.535
and there are a hundred people,
or several hundred people,

00:10:18.535 --> 00:10:20.762
across the world, on the live Internet,

00:10:20.762 --> 00:10:23.248
watching and thinking of what
you're thinking, or perhaps,

00:10:23.248 --> 00:10:24.717
something different.

00:10:24.717 --> 00:10:25.788
And with the Internet, of course,

00:10:25.788 --> 00:10:28.328
we can have millions of minds
melted across the world,

00:10:28.328 --> 00:10:29.686
at the same time.

00:10:29.686 --> 00:10:31.706
So, the question, and this
is, of course, a continuum,

00:10:31.706 --> 00:10:34.484
the question arises, why is
this extended theory of mind

00:10:34.484 --> 00:10:36.147
so well developed in adult humans,

00:10:36.147 --> 00:10:38.527
and apparently, not in other species?

00:10:38.527 --> 00:10:41.418
So, here's my expansion of Danny's idea.

00:10:41.418 --> 00:10:45.258
I suggest that there was a
psychological evolution barrier

00:10:45.258 --> 00:10:48.547
that held back all these
other intelligent species,

00:10:48.547 --> 00:10:51.809
at about this point in the
evolution of theory of mind.

00:10:51.809 --> 00:10:53.751
What might that barrier be?

00:10:53.751 --> 00:10:55.881
We can now come back to the
theme of this symposium,

00:10:55.881 --> 00:10:57.656
and suggest there's also a continuum

00:10:57.656 --> 00:10:59.114
in the awareness of death risk,

00:10:59.114 --> 00:11:01.474
and understanding of personal mortality.

00:11:01.474 --> 00:11:03.427
I may not have my numbers exactly correct,

00:11:03.427 --> 00:11:08.303
but, seems to me that you first
have an automated reaction

00:11:08.303 --> 00:11:11.165
to death risk, which, as Joe pointed out,

00:11:11.165 --> 00:11:14.311
many species, or all species should have.

00:11:14.311 --> 00:11:16.732
Some kind of awareness of death risk.

00:11:16.732 --> 00:11:18.334
And if some kind of self-awareness

00:11:18.334 --> 00:11:19.985
was enhanced at that time,

00:11:19.985 --> 00:11:21.805
you would, maybe, become
aware of the death

00:11:21.805 --> 00:11:23.755
of another individual.

00:11:23.755 --> 00:11:26.753
But, if I substitute
crows for magpies here,

00:11:26.753 --> 00:11:28.350
it's the very same animal birds,

00:11:28.350 --> 00:11:30.173
and birds the seem to evolve

00:11:30.173 --> 00:11:32.288
some kind of awareness
of death we heard about

00:11:32.288 --> 00:11:34.314
earlier in the symposium,

00:11:34.314 --> 00:11:38.715
that seems right on the
cusp of what humans have.

00:11:38.715 --> 00:11:41.150
And yet, just short of it.

00:11:41.150 --> 00:11:43.829
So, the operative word
here, is mortality salience.

00:11:43.829 --> 00:11:46.061
Conscious understanding and realization

00:11:46.061 --> 00:11:48.740
of one's personal mortality.

00:11:48.740 --> 00:11:51.247
So, if we go down this continuum, well,

00:11:51.247 --> 00:11:55.212
death anxiety may require
extended theory of mind.

00:11:55.212 --> 00:11:58.625
Truly understanding the
death of another individual

00:11:58.625 --> 00:12:00.535
would result in
understanding the mortality

00:12:00.535 --> 00:12:02.294
of other individuals.

00:12:02.294 --> 00:12:04.542
And this conscious
awareness would exaggerate

00:12:04.542 --> 00:12:06.282
the systems we've heard about,

00:12:06.282 --> 00:12:09.220
that extensive, and
not just actual events,

00:12:09.220 --> 00:12:10.262
but even thinking about it,

00:12:10.262 --> 00:12:13.173
at the level of
consciousness, as Joe said.

00:12:13.173 --> 00:12:16.737
Such individuals would then have reduction

00:12:16.737 --> 00:12:19.225
in reproductive fitness.

00:12:19.225 --> 00:12:21.245
Evolution doesn't care if you survive.

00:12:21.245 --> 00:12:23.755
Evolution cares if you reproduce.

00:12:23.755 --> 00:12:25.227
And I suspect that those individuals

00:12:25.227 --> 00:12:26.965
who first ran into this barrier,

00:12:26.965 --> 00:12:29.853
and maybe it happened many
times, in many species,

00:12:29.853 --> 00:12:31.743
had reduction in reproductive fitness,

00:12:31.743 --> 00:12:34.074
and could not transmit their genotype.

00:12:34.074 --> 00:12:36.343
So then, the emergence of
extended theory of mind

00:12:36.343 --> 00:12:39.382
would result in awareness of mortality,

00:12:39.382 --> 00:12:43.260
and again, a failure to fix
the genotype in two species.

00:12:43.260 --> 00:12:46.232
We've already said that reality
denial should be negative,

00:12:46.232 --> 00:12:48.932
so, what of these two
unusual, cognitive features

00:12:48.932 --> 00:12:52.252
emerged in the same
minds, at the same time,

00:12:52.252 --> 00:12:54.603
a rare, negative, double-negative,

00:12:54.603 --> 00:12:58.022
which could result sufficient
tolerance of death anxiety,

00:12:58.022 --> 00:13:01.003
to establish the combination of species.

00:13:01.003 --> 00:13:04.164
Thus, perhaps, two rare
evolutionary maladpatations,

00:13:04.164 --> 00:13:06.811
or negatives, could
have coincided to allow

00:13:06.811 --> 00:13:10.314
this mind over reality transition.

00:13:10.314 --> 00:13:11.835
I have a much more extended view of this,

00:13:11.835 --> 00:13:13.443
that we don't have time to discuss.

00:13:13.443 --> 00:13:16.193
(crowd laughing)

00:13:17.572 --> 00:13:19.247
I need to talk to the experts to it,

00:13:19.247 --> 00:13:22.117
before I go any further with that.

00:13:22.117 --> 00:13:23.964
But, "Any theory that makes progress,

00:13:23.964 --> 00:13:26.858
"is bound to be initially
counterintuitive."

00:13:26.858 --> 00:13:29.647
So, I'd like to suggest
that this hypothetical

00:13:29.647 --> 00:13:31.586
singular phase in human evolution,

00:13:31.586 --> 00:13:35.400
which mortality salience and
maladaptive death anxiety

00:13:35.400 --> 00:13:38.830
were triggered by acquiring
extended theory of mind,

00:13:38.830 --> 00:13:42.209
which result in an understanding
of personal mortality.

00:13:42.209 --> 00:13:44.090
But then, one time only,

00:13:44.090 --> 00:13:46.368
were stabilized by
simultaneous acquisition

00:13:46.368 --> 00:13:49.372
of general reality
denial, in the same minds.

00:13:49.372 --> 00:13:51.148
I remember asking Danny, there couldn't be

00:13:51.148 --> 00:13:53.798
a death denial module.

00:13:53.798 --> 00:13:56.257
But, he came to the
same conclusion I have.

00:13:56.257 --> 00:13:58.187
We just deny anything we don't like.

00:13:58.187 --> 00:13:59.867
(crowd laughing)

00:13:59.867 --> 00:14:01.580
So, there are other consequences.

00:14:01.580 --> 00:14:04.674
After-life myths,
superstitions, religiosity,

00:14:04.674 --> 00:14:07.272
self-deception,
over-confidence, risk-taking,

00:14:07.272 --> 00:14:10.502
and last, but not least,
the optimism bias.

00:14:10.502 --> 00:14:13.692
Humans are well known to
be irrationally optimistic.

00:14:13.692 --> 00:14:17.253
Many studies have shown
this, even in fMRI studies.

00:14:17.253 --> 00:14:18.484
And evolutionary modeling...

00:14:18.484 --> 00:14:21.862
(crowd laughing)

00:14:21.862 --> 00:14:24.100
Shows that reacting, in
an overconfident manner,

00:14:24.100 --> 00:14:26.137
can have fitness benefits,

00:14:26.137 --> 00:14:28.082
as long as the contested resources

00:14:28.082 --> 00:14:31.234
are sufficiently large, compared
to the cost of competition.

00:14:31.234 --> 00:14:32.682
Now, if you combine overconfidence

00:14:32.682 --> 00:14:36.849
with extended theory of
mind, you got big success.

00:14:37.892 --> 00:14:39.860
Of course, here's a case, I believe,

00:14:39.860 --> 00:14:41.982
of initially successful, but eventually,

00:14:41.982 --> 00:14:44.399
fatal case of reality denial.

00:14:46.240 --> 00:14:48.220
So, how important is reality denial?

00:14:48.220 --> 00:14:51.322
Let's do a thought
experiment, and delete it.

00:14:51.322 --> 00:14:53.073
Well, some other features of humans,

00:14:53.073 --> 00:14:56.431
would condemn the partially eliminated,

00:14:56.431 --> 00:14:59.960
but let's not dim theory of
mind, and eliminate that.

00:14:59.960 --> 00:15:01.530
And you find that most of these unusual,

00:15:01.530 --> 00:15:03.841
exaggerative cognitive features of humans,

00:15:03.841 --> 00:15:06.839
while they could still be
present, would be greatly dimmed.

00:15:06.839 --> 00:15:09.105
So, I suggested this combination

00:15:09.105 --> 00:15:11.640
could give you this transition,

00:15:11.640 --> 00:15:14.319
which is consistent so
far, with all-known facts,

00:15:14.319 --> 00:15:16.501
compatible with the other theories,

00:15:16.501 --> 00:15:18.380
not negated by currently-known facts,

00:15:18.380 --> 00:15:20.423
but is not not directly testable

00:15:20.423 --> 00:15:22.054
by experimental reproduction,

00:15:22.054 --> 00:15:25.734
or directly falsifiable by
experimental approaches.

00:15:25.734 --> 00:15:27.484
Now, "The great tragedy of science

00:15:27.484 --> 00:15:30.012
"is the slaying of a beautiful hypothesis

00:15:30.012 --> 00:15:33.333
"by an ugly fact."
(crowd laughing)

00:15:33.333 --> 00:15:35.324
And I've been searching for that fact,

00:15:35.324 --> 00:15:38.183
to destroy this hypothesis.

00:15:38.183 --> 00:15:39.843
If you can find it, let me know.

00:15:39.843 --> 00:15:41.884
But, it can't just be, I don't like it.

00:15:41.884 --> 00:15:44.986
(crowd laughing)

00:15:44.986 --> 00:15:48.176
So, when did this occur in
human evolution, finally?

00:15:48.176 --> 00:15:49.877
We know that about two million years ago,

00:15:49.877 --> 00:15:52.498
our ancestors from Africa,
some stayed behind,

00:15:52.498 --> 00:15:54.620
and some spread all across the old world,

00:15:54.620 --> 00:15:57.847
to give rise to neanderthals
and many other species.

00:15:57.847 --> 00:16:01.365
And this went down for
almost two millions years,

00:16:01.365 --> 00:16:04.538
leaving behind many
species and subspecies.

00:16:04.538 --> 00:16:07.286
But, the types of things
that you might think

00:16:07.286 --> 00:16:09.797
might be related to theory of mind,

00:16:09.797 --> 00:16:13.840
reality denial leaves no
signal that I could think of.

00:16:13.840 --> 00:16:16.188
But, symbolic art, complex tool making,

00:16:16.188 --> 00:16:20.821
personal ornamentation,
burials with added materials,

00:16:20.821 --> 00:16:23.760
all occur around 100-to-200,000 years ago.

00:16:23.760 --> 00:16:27.917
Again, the experts would be
much more precise than I am.

00:16:27.917 --> 00:16:29.278
This happens to be about the time

00:16:29.278 --> 00:16:30.593
that the human migration

00:16:30.593 --> 00:16:32.488
and the peopling of the world occurred,

00:16:32.488 --> 00:16:35.376
in which species evolved in Africa,

00:16:35.376 --> 00:16:37.277
and then gradually
spread across the world,

00:16:37.277 --> 00:16:40.157
and essentially took over the planet.

00:16:40.157 --> 00:16:42.676
And we are now, unlike
most of the subspecies,

00:16:42.676 --> 00:16:43.968
where there are multiple species,

00:16:43.968 --> 00:16:48.348
we are the lone survivors and
the masters of the planet.

00:16:48.348 --> 00:16:50.966
So, while we can't be
sure, I'd like to speculate

00:16:50.966 --> 00:16:54.536
that the evolution of
anatomically-modern humans,

00:16:54.536 --> 00:16:56.753
into behaviorally modern humans,

00:16:56.753 --> 00:16:59.064
which is seen in the archeological record,

00:16:59.064 --> 00:17:01.545
although it's quite incomplete,

00:17:01.545 --> 00:17:05.345
may have, at least, partly
involved this transition.

00:17:05.345 --> 00:17:08.865
So, it so happens this theory can provide

00:17:08.865 --> 00:17:11.173
a unifying explanation,

00:17:11.173 --> 00:17:13.811
for several unusual
exaggerated features of humans,

00:17:13.811 --> 00:17:16.792
such as theory of mind, which
is beneficial for many things,

00:17:16.792 --> 00:17:19.663
reality denial, strong
tendency to self-deception

00:17:19.663 --> 00:17:22.458
and false beliefs,
overarching optimism bias,

00:17:22.458 --> 00:17:25.674
risk-taking behavior,
recent emergence, perhaps,

00:17:25.674 --> 00:17:29.943
as the dominant species, and
replacement of everybody else.

00:17:29.943 --> 00:17:33.365
Remember, this would have
to have a genetic basis.

00:17:33.365 --> 00:17:35.084
There are some examples
of supporting evidence

00:17:35.084 --> 00:17:37.275
I don't have time to talk about.

00:17:37.275 --> 00:17:39.371
And issues arising, and future directions,

00:17:39.371 --> 00:17:41.193
I don't have time to talk about, but...

00:17:41.193 --> 00:17:42.351
(crowd laughing)

00:17:42.351 --> 00:17:44.253
I would point out that
some of the brain regions

00:17:44.253 --> 00:17:47.483
involved in optimism
bias, anxiety and so on,

00:17:47.483 --> 00:17:50.864
are related to some of these things.

00:17:50.864 --> 00:17:54.568
So, finally, let me close, by
coming back to Danny Brower.

00:17:54.568 --> 00:17:58.626
From Danny Brower's 2007 draft manuscript,

00:17:58.626 --> 00:18:01.664
"We are polluting the earth
and changing the climate

00:18:01.664 --> 00:18:05.798
"in ways that we can't predict,
and likely at some point,

00:18:05.798 --> 00:18:07.487
"can't easily reverse.

00:18:07.487 --> 00:18:10.828
"If we're so smart, why do
we continue to sow the seeds

00:18:10.828 --> 00:18:12.857
"for our eventual destruction?

00:18:12.857 --> 00:18:14.598
"Perhaps, because we
are saddled with a brain

00:18:14.598 --> 00:18:15.878
"that is designed by selection

00:18:15.878 --> 00:18:18.055
"to cope with the
ultimate disaster, death,

00:18:18.055 --> 00:18:19.846
"by denying that it will occur,

00:18:19.846 --> 00:18:21.875
"and so we treat other impending disasters

00:18:21.875 --> 00:18:24.565
"by denying that they will ever happen.

00:18:24.565 --> 00:18:25.655
"Indeed, it it is arguable

00:18:25.655 --> 00:18:29.067
"that we are destined to
destroy ourselves as a species."

00:18:29.067 --> 00:18:30.658
2007.

00:18:30.658 --> 00:18:32.608
You don't have to listen
to climate scientists,

00:18:32.608 --> 00:18:35.287
just look at the HSBC banks projection

00:18:35.287 --> 00:18:37.046
for what they're gonna run into,

00:18:37.046 --> 00:18:39.651
in terms of extreme weather events.

00:18:39.651 --> 00:18:41.525
Personally, I think this is a case

00:18:41.525 --> 00:18:46.128
where legitimate fear
mongering is appropriate.

00:18:46.128 --> 00:18:48.589
It's global and local climate destruction,

00:18:48.589 --> 00:18:49.710
not just climate change,

00:18:49.710 --> 00:18:51.779
affecting you and everybody
else that you know

00:18:51.779 --> 00:18:53.309
in your backyard.

00:18:53.309 --> 00:18:56.017
Again, this quote I found
in Danny's manuscript,

00:18:56.017 --> 00:18:58.953
"A man who carries a cat by the tail

00:18:58.953 --> 00:19:01.842
"learns something he can
